Key Match Events: Baghdad Bounedjah gave Algeria the lead with a clinical finish after 18 minutes.
Bounedjah's spectacular overhead kick goal was disallowed for offside after a VAR review.
Mabululu equalized for Angola in the 65th minute after his penalty hit the bar and he converted the rebound.
Post-Match Reflections: Algeria endured more Africa Cup of Nations frustration as they were held to a 1-1 draw by Angola.
The Algerians are looking to avoid a similar fate to 2022 when they entered as defending champions but crashed out in the group stages after failing to win a game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Riyad Mahrez proved a constant threat at set-plays during a late spell of pressure.
Angola went into the match on the back of four consecutive goalless draws.
